title: 'pkg/commands Code Review: Result[T] Conformance and Error Handling'
feature_slug: commands-review-fixes
verdict: SUITABLE
suitability_assessment: |
    SUITABLE. The review identified 4 specific issues across 6 files in pkg/commands
    (578 total lines, 92.2% test coverage). All issues are cleanly separable and can
    be fixed in parallel with disjoint file ownership:

    1. **Non-conforming return types**: 7 functions return (*CommandSet, error) or
       ([]string, error) instead of result.Result[T]. All are error-capable functions
       that should use Result[T] for protocol conformance.

    2. **Hardcoded error strings**: 9 fmt.Errorf calls with hardcoded messages instead
       of error codes from pkg/result/codes.go. Need to add E001-E006 command extraction
       error codes and update all error construction to use result.NewFatal.

    3. **ExtractCommands wrapper has 0% test coverage**: wrapper.go:7 ExtractCommands
       is a convenience wrapper used by pkg/engine/runner.go but has no tests. All
       other functions have >80% coverage.

    4. **Priority() methods are infallible but follow signature for interface compliance**:
       All parser Priority() methods return int without error. These are correctly
       exempted from Result[T] migration (no error cases exist).

    Time estimate:
    - Scout: ~5 min
    - Wave 1 execution: ~8 min (3 agents × 3 min avg, accounting for parallelism)
    - Merge & verification: ~3 min
    Total SAW time: ~16 min

    Sequential baseline: ~25 min
    Time savings: ~9 min (36% faster)

    Recommendation: Proceed. The parallelization value is clear (build/test cycle
    >30s for Go module), and the fixes improve protocol conformance across a foundational
    command extraction package used by Scout automation.
test_command: go test ./pkg/commands/...
lint_command: go vet ./pkg/commands/...
