interface_contracts:
    - name: Extract
      description: |
        Extractor.Extract orchestrates priority-based command resolution. Currently
        returns (*CommandSet, error). Must be updated to return Result[ExtractData]
        for protocol conformance.
      definition: |
        // Before:
        func (e *Extractor) Extract(ctx context.Context, repoRoot string) (*CommandSet, error)

        // After:
        type ExtractData struct {
            CommandSet *CommandSet
        }
        func (e *Extractor) Extract(ctx context.Context, repoRoot string) result.Result[ExtractData]
      location: pkg/commands/extractor.go
    - name: ParseCI
      description: |
        CIParser.ParseCI interface method. Currently returns (*CommandSet, error).
        Must be updated to return Result[ParseCIData] for protocol conformance.
      definition: |
        // Before (interface):
        type CIParser interface {
            ParseCI(repoRoot string) (*CommandSet, error)
            Priority() int
        }

        // After (interface):
        type ParseCIData struct {
            CommandSet *CommandSet
        }
        type CIParser interface {
            ParseCI(repoRoot string) result.Result[ParseCIData]
            Priority() int
        }

        // Implementation in GithubActionsParser:
        func (p *GithubActionsParser) ParseCI(repoRoot string) result.Result[ParseCIData]
      location: pkg/commands/types.go (interface), pkg/commands/github_actions.go (implementation)
    - name: ParseBuildSystem
      description: |
        BuildSystemParser.ParseBuildSystem interface method. Currently returns
        (*CommandSet, error). Must be updated to return Result[ParseBuildSystemData]
        for protocol conformance.
      definition: |
        // Before (interface):
        type BuildSystemParser interface {
            ParseBuildSystem(repoRoot string) (*CommandSet, error)
            Priority() int
        }

        // After (interface):
        type ParseBuildSystemData struct {
            CommandSet *CommandSet
        }
        type BuildSystemParser interface {
            ParseBuildSystem(repoRoot string) result.Result[ParseBuildSystemData]
            Priority() int
        }

        // Implementations in MakefileParser and PackageJSONParser:
        func (p *MakefileParser) ParseBuildSystem(repoRoot string) result.Result[ParseBuildSystemData]
        func (p *PackageJSONParser) ParseBuildSystem(repoRoot string) result.Result[ParseBuildSystemData]
      location: pkg/commands/types.go (interface), pkg/commands/makefile.go and pkg/commands/package_json.go (implementations)
    - name: parseWorkflowFile
      description: |
        GithubActionsParser helper that parses a single GitHub Actions workflow file.
        Currently returns ([]string, error). Must be updated to return
        Result[ParseWorkflowData] for protocol conformance.
      definition: |
        // Before:
        func (p *GithubActionsParser) parseWorkflowFile(path string) ([]string, error)

        // After:
        type ParseWorkflowData struct {
            Commands []string
        }
        func (p *GithubActionsParser) parseWorkflowFile(path string) result.Result[ParseWorkflowData]
      location: pkg/commands/github_actions.go
    - name: LanguageDefaults
      description: |
        Variable holding the language defaults implementation. Currently returns
        (*CommandSet, error). Must be updated to return Result[LanguageDefaultsData]
        for protocol conformance. This is a var (not a method) to allow test replacement.
      definition: |
        // Before:
        var LanguageDefaults = func(repoRoot string) (*CommandSet, error)

        // After:
        type LanguageDefaultsData struct {
            CommandSet *CommandSet
        }
        var LanguageDefaults = func(repoRoot string) result.Result[LanguageDefaultsData]

        // Implementation (languageDefaultsImpl):
        func languageDefaultsImpl(repoRoot string) result.Result[LanguageDefaultsData]
      location: pkg/commands/defaults.go
    - name: ExtractCommands
      description: |
        Convenience wrapper for web CLI delegation. Currently returns (*CommandSet, error).
        Must be updated to return Result[ExtractData] for protocol conformance.
      definition: |
        // Before:
        func ExtractCommands(ctx context.Context, repoRoot string) (*CommandSet, error)

        // After:
        func ExtractCommands(ctx context.Context, repoRoot string) result.Result[ExtractData]
      location: pkg/commands/wrapper.go
    - name: Command extraction error codes
      description: |
        New error codes for command extraction failures. Must be added to pkg/result/codes.go
        in the E001-E099 range (command extraction domain).
      definition: |
        // Add to pkg/result/codes.go after existing error code ranges:

        // Command extraction error codes (E001-E099)
        const (
            CodeCommandExtractWorkflowRead   = "E001_WORKFLOW_READ"
            CodeCommandExtractWorkflowParse  = "E002_WORKFLOW_PARSE"
            CodeCommandExtractPackageRead    = "E003_PACKAGE_READ"
            CodeCommandExtractPackageParse   = "E004_PACKAGE_PARSE"
            CodeCommandExtractNoToolchain    = "E005_NO_TOOLCHAIN"
            CodeCommandExtractCancelled      = "E006_EXTRACT_CANCELLED"
        )
      location: pkg/result/codes.go
waves:
    - number: 1
      agents:
        - id: A
          task: |
            **Objective**: Update extractor.go to return Result[ExtractData] and add test coverage for wrapper.go.

            **Files to modify**:
            - pkg/commands/extractor.go (lines 46-101)
            - pkg/commands/extractor_test.go (add new tests)
            - pkg/commands/wrapper.go (line 7)

            **Changes**:

            1. Add ExtractData type before Extract method:
               ```go
               // ExtractData wraps the result of Extract operation
               type ExtractData struct {
                   CommandSet *CommandSet
               }
               ```

            2. Update Extract signature and implementation:
               - Change signature from `func (e *Extractor) Extract(ctx context.Context, repoRoot string) (*CommandSet, error)`
                 to `func (e *Extractor) Extract(ctx context.Context, repoRoot string) result.Result[ExtractData]`
               - Replace `return nil, fmt.Errorf("extraction cancelled: %w", err)` at lines 52 and 70 with
                 `return result.NewFailure[ExtractData]([]result.SAWError{result.NewFatal(result.CodeCommandExtractCancelled, fmt.Sprintf("extraction cancelled: %v", err))})`
               - Replace `return nil, fmt.Errorf("all parsers returned nil and language defaults failed: %w", err)` at line 98 with
                 `return result.NewFailure[ExtractData]([]result.SAWError{result.NewFatal(result.CodeCommandExtractNoToolchain, fmt.Sprintf("all parsers returned nil and language defaults failed: %v", err))})`
               - Replace `return results[0].commandSet, nil` at line 92 with
                 `return result.NewSuccess(ExtractData{CommandSet: results[0].commandSet})`
               - Update LanguageDefaults call at line 96: change `commandSet, err := LanguageDefaults(repoRoot)`
                 to `r := LanguageDefaults(repoRoot); if r.IsFatal() { return result.NewFailure[ExtractData](r.Errors) }; commandSet := r.GetData().CommandSet`
               - Replace final return `return commandSet, nil` at line 100 with
                 `return result.NewSuccess(ExtractData{CommandSet: commandSet})`

            3. Update ExtractCommands wrapper signature and implementation (wrapper.go line 7):
               - Change signature from `func ExtractCommands(ctx context.Context, repoRoot string) (*CommandSet, error)`
                 to `func ExtractCommands(ctx context.Context, repoRoot string) result.Result[ExtractData]`
               - Change implementation from `return e.Extract(ctx, repoRoot)` to `return e.Extract(ctx, repoRoot)` (no change in call, just signature)

            4. Update extractor_test.go to test new return type:
               - Find all test cases calling Extract() and update assertions to use Result[ExtractData]:
                 - Replace `commandSet, err := extractor.Extract(...)` with `r := extractor.Extract(...)`
                 - Replace `if err != nil` checks with `if r.IsFatal()` checks
                 - Replace `commandSet.Toolchain` access with `r.GetData().CommandSet.Toolchain`
               - Add test coverage for ExtractCommands wrapper (currently 0%):
                 ```go
                 func TestExtractCommands(t *testing.T) {
                     // Create temp dir with go.mod
                     tmpDir := t.TempDir()
                     goModPath := filepath.Join(tmpDir, "go.mod")
                     if err := os.WriteFile(goModPath, []byte("module test"), 0644); err != nil {
                         t.Fatal(err)
                     }

                     r := ExtractCommands(context.Background(), tmpDir)
                     if r.IsFatal() {
                         t.Fatalf("expected success, got errors: %v", r.Errors)
                     }
                     if r.GetData().CommandSet.Toolchain != "go" {
                         t.Errorf("expected go toolchain, got %s", r.GetData().CommandSet.Toolchain)
                     }
                 }
                 ```

            **Interface contracts**: See Extract and ExtractCommands contracts above.

            **Verification gate**:
            ```
            go build ./pkg/commands/...
            go vet ./pkg/commands/...
            go test ./pkg/commands/... -run "TestExtract|TestExtractCommands"
            ```

            **Constraints**:
            - Do NOT modify Priority() methods (they are infallible and correctly exempted)
            - Do NOT modify types.go interface definitions (Agent B handles CIParser, Agent C handles BuildSystemParser)
            - Ensure all error paths use result.NewFatal with appropriate error codes
          files:
            - pkg/commands/extractor.go
            - pkg/commands/extractor_test.go
            - pkg/commands/wrapper.go
        - id: B
          task: |
            **Objective**: Update github_actions.go to return Result[ParseCIData] and update CIParser interface.

            **Files to modify**:
            - pkg/commands/github_actions.go (lines 17-68, 77-96)
            - pkg/commands/github_actions_test.go (update all test cases)
            - pkg/commands/types.go (lines 44-48)

            **Changes**:

            1. Update types.go CIParser interface:
               ```go
               // Add new data type:
               type ParseCIData struct {
                   CommandSet *CommandSet
               }

               // Update interface:
               type CIParser interface {
                   ParseCI(repoRoot string) result.Result[ParseCIData]
                   Priority() int
               }
               ```

            2. Add ParseWorkflowData type before parseWorkflowFile method:
               ```go
               // ParseWorkflowData wraps the result of parseWorkflowFile operation
               type ParseWorkflowData struct {
                   Commands []string
               }
               ```

            3. Update ParseCI signature and implementation:
               - Change signature from `func (p *GithubActionsParser) ParseCI(repoRoot string) (*CommandSet, error)`
                 to `func (p *GithubActionsParser) ParseCI(repoRoot string) result.Result[ParseCIData]`
               - Replace `return nil, nil` at line 22 (no .github/workflows dir) with
                 `return result.NewSuccess(ParseCIData{CommandSet: nil})`
               - Replace `return nil, fmt.Errorf("reading workflows directory: %w", err)` at line 28 with
                 `return result.NewFailure[ParseCIData]([]result.SAWError{result.NewFatal(result.CodeCommandExtractWorkflowRead, fmt.Sprintf("reading workflows directory: %v", err))})`
               - Replace `return nil, nil` at line 57 (no commands found) with
                 `return result.NewSuccess(ParseCIData{CommandSet: nil})`
               - Replace final `return cmdSet, nil` at line 68 with
                 `return result.NewSuccess(ParseCIData{CommandSet: cmdSet})`
               - Update parseWorkflowFile call at line 44: change `commands, err := p.parseWorkflowFile(workflowPath)`
                 to `r := p.parseWorkflowFile(workflowPath); if r.IsFatal() { continue }; commands := r.GetData().Commands`

            4. Update parseWorkflowFile signature and implementation:
               - Change signature from `func (p *GithubActionsParser) parseWorkflowFile(path string) ([]string, error)`
                 to `func (p *GithubActionsParser) parseWorkflowFile(path string) result.Result[ParseWorkflowData]`
               - Replace `return nil, fmt.Errorf("reading workflow file: %w", err)` at line 80 with
                 `return result.NewFailure[ParseWorkflowData]([]result.SAWError{result.NewFatal(result.CodeCommandExtractWorkflowRead, fmt.Sprintf("reading workflow file %s: %v", path, err))})`
               - Replace `return nil, fmt.Errorf("parsing YAML: %w", err)` at line 96 with
                 `return result.NewFailure[ParseWorkflowData]([]result.SAWError{result.NewFatal(result.CodeCommandExtractWorkflowParse, fmt.Sprintf("parsing YAML in %s: %v", path, err))})`
               - Replace final `return commands, nil` at line 151 with
                 `return result.NewSuccess(ParseWorkflowData{Commands: commands})`

            5. Update github_actions_test.go to test new return types:
               - Find all test cases calling ParseCI() and update assertions to use Result[ParseCIData]:
                 - Replace `commandSet, err := parser.ParseCI(...)` with `r := parser.ParseCI(...)`
                 - Replace `if err != nil` checks with `if r.IsFatal()` checks
                 - Replace nil checks `if commandSet == nil` with `if r.GetData().CommandSet == nil`
                 - Replace `commandSet.Commands.Build` access with `r.GetData().CommandSet.Commands.Build`

            **Interface contracts**: See ParseCI and parseWorkflowFile contracts above.

            **Verification gate**:
            ```
            go build ./pkg/commands/...
            go vet ./pkg/commands/...
            go test ./pkg/commands/... -run "TestGithubActions"
            ```

            **Constraints**:
            - Do NOT modify Priority() method (it is infallible and correctly exempted)
            - classifyCommands and detectToolchain are pure functions (no error cases), keep as-is
            - Ensure parseWorkflowFile failures are handled gracefully in ParseCI (continue loop, not fatal)
          files:
            - pkg/commands/github_actions.go
            - pkg/commands/github_actions_test.go
            - pkg/commands/types.go
        - id: C
          task: |
            **Objective**: Update makefile.go, package_json.go, and defaults.go to return Result[ParseBuildSystemData] and Result[LanguageDefaultsData].

            **Files to modify**:
            - pkg/commands/makefile.go (lines 14-48)
            - pkg/commands/makefile_test.go (update all test cases)
            - pkg/commands/package_json.go (lines 20-60)
            - pkg/commands/package_json_test.go (update all test cases)
            - pkg/commands/defaults.go (lines 11-115)
            - pkg/commands/defaults_test.go (update all test cases)
            - pkg/commands/types.go (lines 50-54)

            **Changes**:

            1. Update types.go BuildSystemParser interface:
               ```go
               // Add new data type:
               type ParseBuildSystemData struct {
                   CommandSet *CommandSet
               }

               // Update interface:
               type BuildSystemParser interface {
                   ParseBuildSystem(repoRoot string) result.Result[ParseBuildSystemData]
                   Priority() int
               }
               ```

            2. Update MakefileParser.ParseBuildSystem (makefile.go lines 14-48):
               - Change signature from `func (p *MakefileParser) ParseBuildSystem(repoRoot string) (*CommandSet, error)`
                 to `func (p *MakefileParser) ParseBuildSystem(repoRoot string) result.Result[ParseBuildSystemData]`
               - Replace `return nil, nil` at line 19 (no Makefile) with
                 `return result.NewSuccess(ParseBuildSystemData{CommandSet: nil})`
               - Replace `return nil, err` at line 24 (file open error) with
